OL,3,CGeorge Galloway, a deeply divisive
OL,4,Cfigure in UK politics, returns to
OL,5,CParliament
OL,7,FBut his relationship with Labour was
OL,8,Fnot a happy one. As early as 1988, the
OL,9,Fexecutive committee of his
OL,10,Fconstituency party passed a vote of no
OL,11,Fconfidence in him, and he narrowly
OL,12,Fsurvived a selection contest in the
OL,13,Fnext year.
OL,15,FHe was widely criticised over a 1994
OL,16,Fvisit to Iraq when he was filmed
OL,17,Fapparently praising Saddam Hussein for
OL,18,Fhis courage, strength and
OL,19,Findefatigability ` although he always
OL,20,Finsisted his comments were addressed
OL,21,Fto the Iraqi people.
